BODY. Habitus as in close congeners (cf. 
Figs 148, 152
). Ocular area slightly elevated. Thoracic furrow present. Clypeus unmodified. Sternum wider than long (0.50/0.34), unmodified.

PALPS. Very similar to 

C. amapa

(cf. 
Figs 154–155
) but femur proximal process of different shape (
Fig. 164
); procursus with simple, narrow tip, not bifid (
Fig. 159
); bulbal process with distinctive ventral sclerite proximally, without serrated ventral sclerite distally (
Fig. 162
).
